&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Hybrid (El Segundo, CA and/or Burbank/North Hollywood, CA)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Be Doing:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;The Chief People Officer (CPO) is a strategic executive responsible for leading the company’s people strategy in alignment with business objectives. As a key member of the executive leadership team, the CPO will drive organizational effectiveness, talent strategy, culture, and compliance. This role requires a leader who can balance high-performance culture building with the rigor, governance, and transparency.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Executive Leadership &amp;amp; Strategy&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the CEO and Board of Directors (including Compensation Committee) on executive compensation, succession planning, and leadership development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute a comprehensive people strategy aligned with long-term business goals and market expectations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a trusted advisor to senior leadership on organizational design, workforce planning, and change management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Public Company Governance &amp;amp; Compliance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure compliance with all applicable labor laws and regulatory requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Legal and Finance on proxy disclosures, executive compensation reporting, and SEC-related people disclosures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support Board and Compensation Committee materials, including CD&amp;amp;A (Compensation Discussion &amp;amp; Analysis)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee internal controls related to HR processes in alignment with Sarbanes-Oxley (SOX) requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Talent &amp;amp; Performance Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and lead a high-performing HR organization across Talent Acquisition, Total Rewards, HR Business Partners, People Operations, and Learning &amp;amp; Development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee executive and enterprise-wide succession planning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive performance management frameworks tied to company objectives and shareholder value&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Total Rewards &amp;amp; Executive Compensation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and manage competitive compensation and equity programs aligned with public market benchmarks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Compensation Committee on executive compensation philosophy, equity plans, and say-on-pay readiness&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure transparency and competitiveness of compensation practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
